<B><U>How to use Kids Mask Factory</U></B><BR><BR>

<U>Drawing your own mask</U><BR>
Simply move your mouse over the main canvas area and left click while moving the mouse. This will create a freehand line in black. Now you can draw a mask with various lines.<BR>
If you make a mistake click on the Undo button, and draw another freehand lines.<BR>
<BR>
<U>Using Face Parts</U><BR>
A range of predrawn faces parts have been provided to make it easy to create great looking masks.  Use either of the Heads, Ears, Eyes, Mouths, Noses or Other buttons select a face part. For more information about selecting face parts <a href="<% = lstrPGFacePartSelect %>">click here</a>.
